## Troubleshooting

Pod won't start:
  oc describe pod <pod-name> -n biss-automation
  oc logs <pod-name> -c biss-runner -n biss-automation

Chrome crashes inside container:
  Ensure --headless=true and --no-sandbox are set in ChromeOptions.
  The Dockerfile sets DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS and DISPLAY env vars
  which suppress common container Chrome warnings.

DB connection refused:
  Verify VPN is active if Oracle DB is on the internal network.
  Check db.properties was written correctly:
    oc exec <pod> -- cat src/test/resources/db.properties

Maven cache missing:
  Check the PVC is bound:
    oc get pvc biss-maven-cache-pvc -n biss-automation
  If Pending, your cluster may need a StorageClass defined.
  Set storageClassName in openshift-jenkins.yaml.

GitLab clone fails:
  Verify gitlab-credentials are correct.
  If internal GitLab uses a self-signed cert:
    Add git -c http.sslVerify=false to the checkout step, OR
    Trust the cert in the container image.

